main event: A round white object was observed in the clouds in Frankfurt, Germany on June 29, 1965.
interesting points: The object was seen descending and then turning at an angle in front of the observers., The observed speed was much greater than known transportation used in the area., The object appeared only in the clouds with no distinguishable features., The reflection observed may have come from the observers, suggesting a probable natural phenomenon., The total observation duration was noted to be about 3 minutes.
sighted object: a round white object in the clouds
witness description: A Federal Aviation Agency flight inspector who could not identify the object.
